the requested visa in violation of its international legal 
obligations under the agreement 
endorsing the opinion of the legal counsel of the united nations 
rendered on 28 november 1988 
considers that the decision by the government of the united 
states of america the host country constitutes a violation of the 
international legal obligations of the host country under the 
agreement between the united nations and the united states of 
america regarding the headquarters of the united nations 
urges the host country to abide scrupulously by the provisions of 
the headquarters agreement and to reconsider and reverse its 
decision 
requests the secretarygeneral to submit a report on the 
developments in this matter no later than december 1 1988 
