<TEXT>
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev says 
constitutional and electoral reforms are a kind of oxygen to 
revive the body politic but it is unlikely they alone can make his 
society any more democratic 
since the proposed reforms appeared on oct 2223 soviet society 
has been engaged in a remarkable debate over an overhaul of the 
electoral system and the structure of the government that gorbachev 
says is the first big step toward making soviet society into one 
governed by law rather than dictate 
the 1500 members of the supreme soviet parliament today 
overwhelmingly approved the package the amended version of which 
still has not been published in the official press 
gorbachevs promise is a weighty one in a society now reopening 
the emotional and physical scars of josef stalins purges and still 
suffering from a much more recent history of systematic jailing or 
exile of dissidents and overbearing bureaucracy 
but political reforms do not guarantee change 
political repression has been imposed in a soviet system that on 
paper guaranteed citizens rights the communist party has shown no 
interest in sharing power 
and operating in the current system critics have used 
gorbachevs policy of glasnost or greater openness to force 
some changes in his proposals 
political reform is a kind of oxygen needed by the public 
organism gorbachev told the supreme soviet on tuesday the first 
day of a special session to consider the reform package 
if we do not carry out political reform to back up the 
processes that are now under way in the economy the social 
transformation of society and the recuperation in the cultural 
field and fail to radically update the activities of the governing 
councils and our personnel the drive for restructuring will 
inevitably begin to skid he said 
gorbachev said his solution is our own socialist system of 
checks and balances designed to protect society against any 
violations of socialist legality at the highest state level 
he called for the formation of a congress of peoples deputies a 
new 2250member legislative body formed not only in elections from 
geographic districts and ethnic territories but from organizations 
such as the communist party and trade unions 
draft legislation gave the presidency which gorbachev assumed 
oct 1 considerably more power and appeared as well to strengthen 
moscows hand with the 15 republics that make up the soviet union 
the proposals loosened an avalanche of more than 300000 
suggestions from across the soviet union and protests from at least 
a third of the republics that some of the reforms fostered the 
opposite of gorbachevs proclaimed intention to give local 
authorities more power 
in the spirit of glasnost soviet leaders got an earful of 
criticism that led them to amend about half of the almost 120 
articles before introducing them to the supreme soviet on monday in 
two days of rare debate deputies of the supreme soviet offered many 
more 
the discussion itself ill tell you frankly is 
unprecedented soviet vice president anatoly lukyanov told a news 
conference 
