lithuania were close behind but could not push the legislation 
through their parliaments 
the presidium of the national supreme soviet declared estonias 
action unconstitutional 
gorbachev also must rein in the communist party and government 
bureaucracies that are stubbornly resistant to change 
the president told the supreme soviet that many initiatives from 
working people are being lost in bureaucratic mazes or are even 
encountering resistance 
he won approval at the june party conference for a plan to get 
the party out of daytoday management of government and economic 
affairs concentrating instead on setting policy he has called for 
taking power from the moscow and giving it to local economic 
managers along with the responsibility of ensuring they make enough 
money to pay for their operations 
but the soviet leader regularly expresses frustration with both 
the party and government bureaucracys slow pace of change 
