a man trapped in the never summer mountains 
for five days walked to safety three days after his snowmobiling 
companion died of an apparent heart attack 
jim edson 38 stumbled onto a logging road wednesday morning 
where he was picked up by a truck driver he and ray owens 65 had 
traveled to the snowwhipped mountains 50 miles northwest of denver 
last friday on an afternoon snowmobile outing 
owens died sunday and edson waited two more days in vain to be 
rescued before walking out on his own 
in recounting the ordeal from a hospital bed in granby edson 
said the mens snowmobiles became mired the day they left in a 
highcountry gulch 16 miles northwest of grand lake 
when it became obvious the weather was not going to clear up 
and they werent coming after us i decided to go out the way we 
came edson said 
heavy winds had drifted snow over their tracks and it took edson 
nearly five hours to walk about two miles through snow up to 2 feet 
deep before he came to the logging road 
