snowmobile and cranked an engine using a sparkplug to light the 
cardboard 
the first night or two when ray was still alive we traded 
turns taking care of the fire after he died id build the fire up 
and the smoke would blow in my face and choke me when it was getting 
low and id wake up again 
before he died sunday owens wanted to try again to get out 
he said lets go real slow but we didnt get more than 15 
feet from the camp and he decided he wasnt going edson said 
owens collapsed about noon sunday and died 
after owens death edson decided to stay where we were at and 
wait to be rescued at one point he heard a plane overhead but 
the weather was too bad for the pilot to see them even with a smoky 
fire 
