<TEXT>
benazir bhuttos selection as prime 
minister triumphantly ended an 11year effort to restore her family 
name and pakistani democracy 
at 35 she also becomes one of the worlds youngest heads of 
government and the first woman prime minister to lead a moslem 
nation in modern times 
ms bhutto who was educated at harvard and oxford inherits the 
political mantle of her father the late prime minister zulfikar ali 
bhutto who was ousted by gen mohammed zia ulhaq in a 1977 coup 
and hanged two years later 
zias death in an aug 17 plane crash made ms bhutto who had 
pledged to restore democracy the nations only nationally 
recognized political leader 
although a daughter of affluence ms bhuttos appeal lies mainly 
among the poor masses of this countrys 107 million people they are 
the strength of her leftleaning pakistan peoples party which 
captured the most seats in the nov 16 national assembly elections 
ms bhutto drew massive adoring crowds during her campaign for 
the countrys first free elections since her fathers death 
mindful of moslem and local custom she always is clad in 
traditional clothes with a scarf draped over her head 
the poised and articulate leader who speaks english fluently 
shocked her western friendsby consenting to an arranged marriage 
last december with karachi businessman asif ali zardari 
ms bhutto who has kept her maiden name was groomed for 
politics by her doting father as the eldest of his four children he 
sent her to study government and politics at harvard in the united 
states then at oxford 
it was at the british university that she tasted her first 
political success when she was elected president of the prestigious 
oxford union debating society in 1976 
the prime ministers post is ms bhutto first paying job her 
only previous employment began in early 1977 as a nonpaid trainee 
in the foreign ministry 
it was shortlived however as zia toppled her fathers 
government a few months later on the pretext that elections that 
year were rigged 
bhutto was hanged in 1979 after his conviction for helping plot 
the murder of a political foe a charge his family has denied 
despite years of detention and foreign exile during zias 
authoritarian rule ms bhutto and her mother nusrat kept the 
party alive as zias disenfranchised opposition 
