assassination of prime minister indira gandhi news reports said 
a panel of five justices granted a stay of execution for satwant 
singh a guard who shot mrs gandhi and kehar singh convicted of 
conspiracy 
the two were scheduled to hang friday but the supreme court 
agreed to stay the execution until tuesday in order to hear 
arguments on a petition filed by kehar singhs son 
they are not related members of the sikh faith use the name 
singh which means lion 
the petition challenges president ramaswamy venkataramans 
refusal to grant clemency to his father without reviewing the merits 
of the case united news of india and press trust of india reported 
venkataraman last week said he could not go into the merits of a 
case already decided by the supreme court the petition filed by 
rajinder singh however contends the constitution gives the 
president such powers the news agencies said 
the judges also stayed satwant singhs execution after his lawyer 
appealed against another high court decision dismissing his appeals 
earlier in the day 
two sikh bodyguards satwant singh and beant singh shot mrs 
gandhi in the garden of her residence on oct 31 1984 
she was apparently killed in retaliation for an army raid she 
ordered four months earlier to rout militants from the golden 
temple the sikhs holiest shrine more than 1200 people died most 
of them sikhs 
beant singh was killed in a shootout with other security guards 
and is revered as a martyr by many militant sikhs 
kehar singh beants uncle was arrested a month later and 
charged with helping to plot mrs gandhis murder which triggered 
antisikh riots across northern india by members of the majority 
hindu religion more than 2700 people died nearly all of them 
sikhs 
sikh violence since then has escalated more than 2300 people 
have died this year alone in northern punjab state where sikhs are 
fighting for an independent homeland 
authorities had ordered increased security in the capital and in 
punjab fearing the executions could trigger a new outbreak of 
communal violence 
kehar singh 54 and satwant singh 30 have been held at the 
maximumsecurity tihar central jail in new delhi since their arrests 
in 1984 
their eightmonth trial ended on jan 22 1986 the convictions 
and death sentences were subsequently upheld by an appeals court and 
by the supreme court 
