office thursday and promised to push for political and economic 
modernization as opponents protested his inauguration in congress 
and in the streets 
salinas a 40yearold economist succeeds president miguel de la 
madrid for a sixyear term he inherits an economy threatened by 
both recession and inflation growth squeezed by a 102 billion 
foreign debt and a population impatient after six years of 
austerity that reduced earnings about 50 percent 
i take office in a complex hour it is a singular moment in 
our history heavy with risks but rich in opportunity salinas 
said in his inaugural address he said he would govern for all 
mexicans and promised nationalist democratic and popular 
reforms 
he said efforts to reduce mexicos foreign debt would begin 
immediately 
