will wilt democracy political competition will turn into social 
conflict and frustrate aims for social justice 
salinas said negotiations will begin at once on mexicos debt 
aimed at cutting debt payments to a level that will leave the 
country with enough money to invest in development and growth 
we will look for new equilibriums with the united states an 
area of opportunities and delicate differences salinas said 
us secretary of state george shultz had an afternoon meeting 
with salinas and praised his inaugural address he told reporters 
salinas felt good chemistry existed between himself and 
presidentelect george bush 
in an unusual arrangement opposition leaders were permitted to 
make televised speeches questioning salinas election before the 
inauguration in return they agreed not to disrupt the actual 
ceremony 
although the speeches were televised walkouts and protest signs 
were not shown cameras also avoided showing the brief violence in 
the zocalo 
the new president outlined a vision of modern mexico in keeping 
with his free market ideas in which a paternalistic state would 
give way to a partnership of political parties business labor 
citizens groups and the church 
democratic front delegate marcela lombardo said in her speech 
that mexicans had actually voted for a radically different 
program 
in his campaign cardenas called for increased government control 
of the economy and a moratorium on debt payments 
according to official figures salinas won barely more than 50 
percent of the vote cardenas won 31 percent and national action 
candidate manuel clouthier 17 percent 
during his speech salinas introduced heads of government 
attending the biggest rounds of applause went to presidents fidel 
castro of cuba and daniel ortega of nicaragua 
also there were presidents virgilio barco of colombia raul 
alfonsin of argentina jose napoleon duarte of el salvador jose 
azcona hoyo of honduras and vinicio cerezo arevalo of guatemala and 
prime minister manuel esquivel of belize 
the us delegation included bushs son john and johns 
mexicanamerican wife columba 
