but that hcfa felt it was worthwile to compile it in a single report 
according to the survey nearly 43 percent of the homes failed to 
meet sanitary standards for food almost 30 percent failed to meet 
standards for maintaining residents personal cleanliness and 29 
percent failed to administer drugs according to doctors orders 
however the report also said that only a small percentage of the 
nursing homes failed to meet standards in many other categories 
