<TEXT>
american telephone amp telegraph co said thursday 
it will post the first annual loss in its 103year history as a 
result of a 67 billion pretax charge that covers the costs of 
scrapping outdated equipment and moving retiring or laying off 
16000 employees 
wall street saw the giant charge as a sign that atampt was moving 
aggressively to cut costs and install a new digital network to meet 
the competition the stock was fairly stable falling 50 cents to 
2937 a share in consolidated new york stock exchange trading 
the charge will not affect atampts cash flow its ability to pay 
dividends or the money available for investment 
this reflects the adjustment of going from a regulated 
marketplace to a competitive marketplace said robert morris iii 
a san franciscobased analyst for goldman sachs amp co 
atampt said the charge would reduce its aftertax profits by 39 
billion that makes it likely that the company will lose about 16 
billion in all of 1988 and 33 billion in the fourth quarter alone 
the only larger quarterly losses in us history were atampts own 
487 billion loss in the fourth quarter of 1983 which involved a 
charge to prepare for the bell system breakup and texaco incs 
476 billion loss in the fourth quarter of 1987 stemming from its 
legal fight with pennzoil co 
longdistance phone companies have been moving aggressively to 
replace their oldfashioned analog equipment with new digital 
equipment that provides higher quality and is better suited to 
custom services and transmission of computer data 
the bulk of the charge 50 billion is to reflect on the books 
the lower value of outdated analog network equipment the remaining 
17 billion is for the costs of removing the outdated equipment 
writedowns in the value of related equipment and reductions in 
employment 
atampt said it would reduce the number of its network employees by 
10000 and the number of its operators by 6000 over the next few 
years 
atampt does not yet know how many of the employees will be given 
jobs elsewhere in the company because that depends on the companys 
growth spokeswoman luann gardner said 
the communications workers of america the union representing 
135000 atampt workers issued a statement saying nonmanagement 
employees have suffered the loss of 78500 jobs since 1984 while 
management ranks have risen by 13600 
this company just has not bitten the bullet it has not come 
out of its monopoly cocoon levels of management the union said 
atampt spokesman burke stinson responded that the company had to 
hire whitecollar workers because of its new thrusts into computers 
and foreign markets but he said were not blind to the fact 
that staff jobs need to be cut 
atampt has a freeze on hiring over most of the company that gives 
the displaced employees a better chance to find work elsewhere 
within the company than if they had to face competition from new 
hires 
plans to reduce 3000 of the network jobs and all 6000 of the 
operator service jobs had already been announced to employees atampt 
said the company is setting aside 400 million to cover the cost of 
redeploying them or giving them payments or incentives related to 
separation from the company by retirement or resignation 
the job cuts are possible because improvements in the network 
reduce the need for maintenance engineering service order 
processing and call handling operators at new stations are able to 
handle 25 percent more calls per hour the company said 
atampt has switched over to a digital network far more rapidly than 
it had previously planned 
the company predicted early in 1987 that it would take until the 
year 2010 to have an alldigital network by the end of 1987 it said 
it could do the job by 1991 on thursday it said it could do the 
job by the end of next year 
mci communications corp and us sprint communications co the 
no 2 and no 3 competitors in long distance have also moved 
rapidly to put in digital networks and have taken big charges to 
write down the book value of their outdated analog equipment 
executives of atampt had said in october that writedowns in the 
fourth quarter could be substantial by taking the pain of the 
writedown all at once atampt no longer has to lower its quarterly 
profits to reflect the costs of depreciating the older equipment 
we view this as very positive news ms gardner said our 
network will continue to be the best out there 
atampt took a 10 billion pretax charge at the end of 1983 to 
